# Copy to .env to override defaults. For Docker Compose this file is OPTIONAL —
# the stack works out of the box without it (SearXNG is bundled and wired
# automatically).
#
# Docker Compose:
#   - SEARXNG_URL is set by compose to the bundled service (http://searxng:8080)
#     and overrides whatever you put here, so you normally don't touch it.
#   - MCP_PORT changes the published MCP port (default 9555). The bundled
#     SearXNG is internal-only (no host port), so there is nothing else to set.
#
# Local (pip/uv) usage:
#   - SEARXNG_URL should point at your own SearXNG instance (JSON output enabled).
SEARXNG_URL=http://localhost:8888
MCP_PORT=9555
# SEARXNG_USERNAME=
# SEARXNG_PASSWORD=
